────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

Ares is a read-only system audit tool.  It does NOT modify the system it
runs on.  However:

  • Audit findings may include sensitive information about the host
    (open ports, services, failed login sources, kernel version).
    Treat the report as you would any other security artifact —
    don't paste it into public chat.
  • The "fix hints" in the report are suggestions, not commands run
    by Ares.  You are responsible for verifying any change you make
    in response.
  • Run Ares only on systems you own or are authorised to audit.
    Unauthorised auditing of systems may violate computer-misuse
    statutes including the Irish Criminal Justice (Offences Against
    Information Systems) Act 2017, the UK Computer Misuse Act 1990,
    and the US Computer Fraud and Abuse Act.

The author disclaims any liability for misuse.  See the disclaimer above.
